---
import AdUnit from './_components/AdUnit.astro';
import HeraldShell from './_components/HeraldShell.astro';
---

<HeraldShell title="About" activePage="about" breadcrumbs={[{ label: 'Home', href: '/l1/news/' }, { label: 'About' }]}>

  <div class="pageTitle">About the Mountainhome Herald</div>

  <div class="twoCol clearfix">
    <div class="mainCol">
      <div class="formSection">
        <strong>History</strong>
        <table class="aspNetTable" style="width:100%; margin-top:10px;">
          <tr><td colspan="2" class="headerRow">Publication History</td></tr>
          <tr>
            <td style="width:180px;"><span class="aspNetLabelBold">Founded:</span></td>
            <td>Year 89 of the Grand Duchy Calendar</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="alternatingRow">
            <td><span class="aspNetLabelBold">Founder:</span></td>
            <td>Urist McDwarfquill, Master Lithographer of the Third Deep</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><span class="aspNetLabelBold">Current Edition:</span></td>
            <td>Rolling News Cycle (transitioned from edition-based Year 312)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="alternatingRow">
            <td><span class="aspNetLabelBold">Headquarters:</span></td>
            <td>Z-Level 2, Room 301, Mountainhome Civic Quarter</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><span class="aspNetLabelBold">Publication Frequency:</span></td>
            <td>Continuous rolling news cycle; suspended during siege conditions</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="alternatingRow">
            <td><span class="aspNetLabelBold">Circulation:</span></td>
            <td>Approximately 4,200 subscribers (carved stone edition + rune-wire distribution)</td>
          </tr>
        </table>
        <p style="margin-top:10px; font-size:11px; line-height:1.5;">
          The Mountainhome Herald was established in Year 89 when Urist McDwarfquill, frustrated by the unreliability
          of goblin-transmitted rumours, carved the first edition onto slate tablets in his workshop on Z-Level 2.
          The Herald has since grown into the Grand Duchy's most widely read independent news source, covering
          politics, crime, economics, culture, sports, and weather across all fortress levels.
        </p>
        <p style="font-size:11px; line-height:1.5;">
          The Herald survived the Siege of Year 204, the Great Magma Flood of Year 251, and two changes of Grand Duke,
          maintaining editorial independence throughout. In Year 309 it transitioned from stone-carved tablets to
          rune-wire distribution, making same-day delivery to all z-levels possible for the first time. In Year 312,
          the Herald adopted a rolling news model, publishing stories as they break rather than in fixed daily editions.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="adSlot--inline">
        <AdUnit size="banner" adId="DSN-BAN-003" text="Support Independent Journalism &mdash; Subscribe to the Herald" cta="Subscribe Now" placement="about_inline" />
      </div>

      <div class="formSection">
        <strong>Editorial Policy</strong>
        <p style="font-size:11px; line-height:1.5;">
          The Mountainhome Herald is committed to accurate, timely, and impartial reporting on all matters
          affecting the citizens of the Grand Duchy of Eldoria. The Herald operates independently of the
          Arcane Council, the Grand Duke's office, and all registered guilds and commercial entities.
        </p>
        <p style="font-size:11px; line-height:1.5;">
          All articles are subject to review by the Editor-in-Chief prior to publication. Corrections are
          published as updates to the original article with a visible "UPDATED" timestamp. Letters to the Editor must be submitted in Dwarven Standard Script
          and are subject to length restrictions (maximum 200 runes). The Herald does not publish anonymous
          submissions from goblin sources.
        </p>
        <p style="font-size:11px; line-height:1.5;">
          The Herald accepts no advertising from entities currently under indictment by the Fortress Guard,
          nor from known associates of the Undead Commerce League. Sponsored content, where it appears,
          is clearly marked with the designation "PAID STONE."
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="formSection">
        <strong>Quick Links</strong>
        <table class="aspNetTable" style="width:100%; margin-top:10px;">
          <tr>
            <th style="width:200px;">Page</th>
            <th>Description</th>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><a href="/l1/news/staff">Editorial Staff</a></td>
            <td>Meet our reporters, their beats, biographies, and direct contact information</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="alternatingRow">
            <td><a href="/l1/news/contact">Contact Us</a></td>
            <td>Department contacts, subscription options, news tips, advertising rates</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><a href="/l1/news/articles">Article Archive</a></td>
            <td>Search all Herald articles by keyword, category, or date range</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="alternatingRow">
            <td><a href="/l1/taxes/">Registry of Deeds</a></td>
            <td>Search property deeds, mortgages, and liens in the Arcane Registry</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><a href="/l1/scoretap/">ScoreTap</a></td>
            <td>Live scores and event coverage for fortress athletics</td>
          </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="sidebarCol">
      <div class="sidebarBox">
        <h4>HERALD OFFICES</h4>
        <img class="sidebarImg" src="https://picsum.photos/seed/heraldoffice/190/130" alt="Herald press room, Z-Level 2" />
        <div class="sidebarContent">
          Z-Level 2, Room 301<br/>
          Press Quarter, Mountainhome<br/><br/>
          M-F 7:00 AM &ndash; 6:00 PM<br/><br/>
          <a href="/l1/news/contact">Full contact details &raquo;</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="adSlot--inline" style="margin:10px 15px 10px 5px;">
        <AdUnit size="rectangle" adId="DSN-REC-003" text="Stonecleave &amp; Gemcutter LLP &mdash; Fortress Law Specialists" cta="Free Consultation" placement="about_sidebar" />
      </div>

      <div class="sidebarBox">
        <h4>EDITORIAL STAFF</h4>
        <div class="sidebarContent">
          Six full-time editorial staff covering all fortress beats.<br/><br/>
          <a href="/l1/news/staff">Meet the team &raquo;</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="sidebarBox">
        <h4>SUBSCRIBE</h4>
        <div class="sidebarContent">
          <strong>Carved stone:</strong> 15 GP/year<br/>
          <strong>Rune-wire:</strong> 8 GP/year<br/><br/>
          <a href="/l1/news/contact">Subscribe &raquo;</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div style="clear:both;"></div>
</HeraldShell>
